```js
let timer;
searchInput.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
  clearTimeout(timer);
  timer = setTimeout(() => {
    fetchResults(e.target.value); // only fires after 300ms of silence
  }, 300);
});
```

**Debounce vs. throttle:** Debounce waits for inactivity. Throttle fires at most once per interval regardless. For search inputs, debounce is almost always the right choice since you only care about the final query.

